description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to work in Trust Grade Junior Doctor post to cover maternity leave.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working in a well-established and supportive, multi-disciplinary team under the supervision of a Clinical Supervisor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will also work on a 1:13 rota which includes weekends and nights.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will be suitable for Doctors with at least 4 months&#39; experience in Psychiatry/ those who are hoping to get further experience in Psychiatry/those wishing to take a break from training or to those aspiring to improve their cv with hands-on Psychiatry experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once in post, as a Trust, we support your training as a priority. Although this appointment is not recognised as a training post, the post holder will be given the same training opportunities as trainees appointed through Health Education East Midlands. You will be supported in maintaining your training portfolio&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All candidates will need to have excellent communication skills, hold full GMC registration without conditions and a license to practice at the time of appointment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Ritu Gupta, Assistant Director of Medical Education&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ritu.gupta1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01246 293289 x 30330&lt;/p&gt;
